&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community Reinvestment Act (CRA) Officer is responsible for the leadership, strategic direction, and administration of the Bank’s CRA program. This role involves high-level strategy, specifically developing, implementing and managing the Bank’s CRA Strategic Plan, while overseeing data reporting, community partnership development, and examination management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the development, implementation, and multi-year management and monitoring of the Bank’s CRA Strategic Plan. Ensure goals are measurable, attainable, and aligned with the bank’s business model.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide quarterly reporting on performance against goals, emerging regulatory risks, and community impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update the CRA Policy and Public File, ensuring full transparency and compliance with applicable rules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and manage high-impact relationships with Community Development Financial Institutions (CDFIs), non-profits, and government agencies to identify and facilitate Qualified Investments and Community Development Loans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop creative service opportunities for staff that leverage the Bank’s unique technology expertise to benefit Low-to-Moderate Income (LMI) individuals and small businesses and LMI communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ongoing community needs assessments to ensure the Bank’s CRA activities are responsive to the specific needs of its Assessment Area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the timely and accurate annual filing of CRA data in accordance with regulatory deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the administration of CRA examinations and serve as the primary point of contact for regulators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Internal Audit and third-party reviewers to proactively identify and remediate program weaknesses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in banking compliance, with at least 5 years focused on CRA management at a $2B+ institution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert-level knowledge of the CRA and fair lending (ECOA/UDAAP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of developing or managing a CRA Strategic Plan is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with managing the CRA compliance examination process and engaging with regulators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in business administration, finance, public policy or related field. CRCM (Certified Regulatory Compliance Manager) designation is strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
