&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, evaluate, and champion new applications for AI that improve platform reliability, developer productivity, and engineering velocity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent engineering in cross-functional AI governance and vendor discussions, ensuring platform and engineering perspectives are well-represented.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build internal expertise and advocacy around AI — running demos, sharing learnings, and helping teams understand where and how to apply AI responsibly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Strategy &amp;amp; Architecture&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in architecture, technology, tooling, and process — and take ownership of addressing them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that new platform systems and services are sensible, secure, scalable, and aligned with Enova-wide design principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct or lead proof-of-concept efforts with the goal of widening Enova&#39;s technology advantages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Team Leadership &amp;amp; Influence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
